docstring:
Test disabling all forward channels and verifying signal suppression.
    
    This test verifies that when all forward channels are disabled, no RF signal
    is transmitted through any channel path. This ensures proper channel control
    and isolation when channels are in the disabled state.
    
    Test Steps:
        1. Configure a channel with disable flag set to turn off all channels
        2. Send disable command to SoCAN device
        3. For each RF matrix channel path:
            a. Switch RF matrix to the channel
            b. Take measurement and screenshot
            c. Verify peak amplitude is below noise threshold
    
    Parameters:
        socan_command_generator: SoCAN command interface
        rf_matrix_command_generator: RF matrix control interface
        keysight_xsan_command_generator: Spectrum analyzer interface
        fwd_address: Forward channel address for SoCAN communication
        my_results: Results storage object for test data
    
    Pass Criteria:
        - Peak amplitude must be less than -40 dBm (background noise level)
        - All RF matrix channel paths must show suppressed signals
        - No channel should transmit when globally disabled
    
    Raises:
        # assertionError: If any channel shows signal above noise threshold when disabled
